# Testing Rules for NestJS Starter

## Test Structure

1. Organize tests by module
2. Use descriptive test names
3. Keep tests isolated and independent
4. Use mocks for external dependencies
5. Place test data in separate files

## Test Best Practices

1. Use before/after hooks for setup and teardown
2. Avoid hardcoded values
3. Use assertions effectively
4. Mock external dependencies when needed
5. Keep tests fast and reliable

## Test Documentation

1. Document test cases
2. Add comments for complex test logic
3. Keep documentation up to date
4. Use README files for test suites
5. Provide examples for common test patterns 